Templates.template:
new sap.collaboration.components.socialprofile.Component(
	"${sId}", // string
	{
		id: ${id}, // sap.ui.core.ID
		models: ${models}, // object
		bindingContexts: ${bindingContexts}, // object
		objectBindings: ${objectBindings}, // object
		metadataContexts: ${metadataContexts}, // object
		validationSuccess: [function (oEvent) {}, this], // function|array
		validationError: [function (oEvent) {}, this], // function|array
		parseError: [function (oEvent) {}, this], // function|array
		formatError: [function (oEvent) {}, this], // function|array
		modelContextChange: [function (oEvent) {}, this], // function|array
		componentData: ${componentData}, // any
		placement: ${sap.m.PlacementType.Auto}, // sap.m.PlacementType
		memberId: "${memberId}", // string
		memberInfo: ${memberInfo}, // object
		openingControl: ${openingControl}, // object
		height: ${"380px"}, // sap.ui.core.CSSSize
		width: ${"300px"} // sap.ui.core.CSSSize
	}
)
Templates.constructorDescription:
Constructor for the Social Profile Component. !!! EXPERIMENTAL !!! Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. If the name of a setting is ambiguous (e.g. a property has the same name as an event), then the framework assumes property, aggregation, association, event in that order. To override this automatic resolution, one of the prefixes "aggregation:", "association:" or "event:" can be added to the name of the setting (such a prefixed name must be enclosed in single or double quotes). The supported settings are:
  • Properties
    • {@link #getPlacement placement} : sap.m.PlacementType (default: sap.m.PlacementType.Auto)
    • {@link #getMemberId memberId} : string
    • {@link #getMemberInfo memberInfo} : {object}
    • {@link #getOpeningControl openingControl} : {object}
    • {@link #getHeight height} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 380px)
    • {@link #getWidth width} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 300px)

Templates.constructorDescription:
Constructor for the Social Timeline Component. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. If the name of a setting is ambiguous (e.g. a property has the same name as an event), then the framework assumes property, aggregation, association, event in that order. To override this automatic resolution, one of the prefixes "aggregation:", "association:" or "event:" can be added to the name of the setting (such a prefixed name must be enclosed in single or double quotes). The supported settings are:

    • {@link #getShowIcons showIcons} : boolean (default: true)

  • Events
